ABUJA – The Federal Government is set to commission the Gari Irriga­tion Project located in Kano and Jigawa States on Wednesday this week. This is in line with the commitment of President Mu­hammadu Buhari towards the diversification of the economy, ensuring food security and en­hancing the welfare of Nigeri­ans. This information was con­tained in a statement on Monday by the Management of the Feder­al Ministry of Water Resources, and signed by the Permanent Secretary, Mrs.Didi Esther Wal­son-Jack. According to the statement, the Minister of Water Resourc­es, Engr. Suleiman Adamu will commission the Project at the Gari Irrigation Project Site.